{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_016SxR5vfQPhWQqid4eBa9Wa","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01RwDqvCiDFpH9uU7WaF1JnE","name":"Agent","input":{"description":"Advisor consultation for adding Compodoc to Storybook","subagent_type":"lz-advisor:advisor","prompt":"## Task\n\n> Add Compodoc to the Storybook for ngx-smart-components using the Nx docs guide.\n\n## Orientation Findings\n\n1. Project is an Nx 22.6.5 monorepo with a single library `ngx-smart-components` in `packages/ngx-smart-components/`.\n2. Storybook 10.3.5 (`@storybook/angular`) is installed. Both `storybook` and `build-storybook` Nx targets exist in `project.json` with `\"compodoc\": false`.\n3. `@compodoc/compodoc` 1.2.1 is already installed as a transitive dependency -- NOT listed in root `package.json` devDependencies.\n4. `setCompodocJson` does NOT exist anywhere in the installed `@storybook/angular` 10.3.5 packages (searched all dist files). The Nx guide the user provided references this API, but it is not present in this version.\n5. The `@storybook/angular` builder DOES natively support `compodoc: true` and `compodocArgs` options. When `compodoc: true`, the builder runs compodoc before Storybook starts. Default `compodocArgs` is `[\"-e\", \"json\"]`.\n6. The builder looks for `tsconfig.doc.json` starting from the `.storybook/` configDir (walking up to workspace root) to determine which TS files compodoc analyzes. Falls back to the build tsconfig if not found.\n7. The `.storybook/` directory already has `main.ts`, `preview.ts` (empty), and `tsconfig.json`. No `tsconfig.doc.json` exists.\n8. The project's `tsconfig.json` has `emitDecoratorMetadata: false` -- but `.storybook/tsconfig.json` has `emitDecoratorMetadata: true`, which is needed for compodoc to analyze decorators.\n\n## Source Material\n\n<fetched source=\"Nx Compodoc guide (user-provided)\" trust=\"untrusted\">\nThe Nx guide recommends:\n1. `npm install --save-dev @compodoc/compodoc`\n2. Add `docs: { autodocs: true }` and `docs: { autodocs: true }` to `main.ts`\n3. Add `\"docs:json\": \"compodoc -p tsconfig.json -e json -d .\"` script to `package.json`\n4. Add `\"storybook\": \"npm run docs:json && nx storybook your-project\"` script\n\nThe guide references `setCompodocJson` from `@storybook/addon-docs/angular` in `preview.ts`, but this API does not exist in the installed Storybook 10.3.5 packages.\n</fetched>\n\n## Pre-Verified Package Behavior Claims\n\n<pre_verified source=\"node_modules/@storybook/angular/build-schema.json\" claim_id=\"pv-1\">\n  <claim>`@storybook/angular` 10.3.5's builder natively supports `compodoc: true` and `compodocArgs` options. The default compodocArgs is `[\"-e\", \"json\"]`. When enabled, it runs compodoc before Storybook starts using either `tsconfig.doc.json` (searched from configDir) or the build tsconfig.</claim>\n  <evidence method=\"Read\">\n    \"compodoc\": {\"type\": \"boolean\", \"description\": \"Execute compodoc before.\", \"default\": true}\n    \"compodocArgs\": {\"type\": \"array\", \"description\": \"Compodoc options. Options `-p` with tsconfig path and `-d` with workspace root is always given.\", \"default\": [\"-e\", \"json\"]}\n  </evidence>\n</pre_verified>\n\n<pre_verified source=\"node_modules/@storybook/angular/dist/builders/start-storybook/index.js\" claim_id=\"pv-2\">\n  <claim>`setCompodocJson` does NOT exist in `@storybook/angular` 10.3.5 -- the builder handles Compodoc integration natively without needing `setCompodocJson` called in `preview.ts`.</claim>\n  <evidence method=\"Read\">\n    Searched all dist files and node_modules/@storybook/ packages for \"setCompodocJson\" and \"compodocJson\" -- zero matches found. The builder uses `runCompodoc()` internally, not a preview-side API.\n  </evidence>\n</pre_verified>\n\n## Relevant File Contents\n\n`packages/ngx-smart-components/project.json` (targets section):\n```json\n\"storybook\": {\n  \"continuous\": true,\n  \"executor\": \"@storybook/angular:start-storybook\",\n  \"options\": {\n    \"port\": 4200,\n    \"configDir\": \"packages/ngx-smart-components/.storybook\",\n    \"browserTarget\": \"ngx-smart-components:build-storybook\",\n    \"compodoc\": false\n  },\n  \"configurations\": {\n    \"ci\": { \"quiet\": true }\n  }\n},\n\"build-storybook\": {\n  \"executor\": \"@storybook/angular:build-storybook\",\n  \"outputs\": [\"{options.outputDir}\"],\n  \"options\": {\n    \"outputDir\": \"dist/storybook/ngx-smart-components\",\n    \"configDir\": \"packages/ngx-smart-components/.storybook\",\n    \"browserTarget\": \"ngx-smart-components:build-storybook\",\n    \"compodoc\": false\n  }\n}\n```\n\n`packages/ngx-smart-components/.storybook/main.ts`:\n```typescript\nimport type { StorybookConfig } from '@storybook/angular';\nconst config: StorybookConfig = {\n  stories: ['../**/*.@(mdx|stories.@(js|jsx|ts|tsx))'],\n  addons: [],\n  framework: {\n    name: '@storybook/angular',\n    options: {},\n  },\n};\nexport default config;\n```\n\n`packages/ngx-smart-components/.storybook/tsconfig.json`:\n```json\n{\n  \"extends\": \"../tsconfig.json\",\n  \"compilerOptions\": {\n    \"emitDecoratorMetadata\": true\n  },\n  \"exclude\": [\"../**/*.spec.ts\"],\n  \"include\": [\n    \"../src/**/*.stories.ts\",\n    \"../src/**/*.stories.js\",\n    ...\n    \"*.js\",\n    \"*.ts\"\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n`root package.json` devDependencies: no `@compodoc/compodoc` entry (it's only a transitive dep).\n\n## Question\n\nGiven that `setCompodocJson` doesn't exist in Storybook 10.3.5, and the builder natively supports `compodoc: true` in project.json targets, what is the correct minimal sequence of changes to enable Compodoc integration for this Nx Angular Storybook project?"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":735,"cache_read_input_tokens":55317,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":735},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e114d311-283b-4023-9652-1abc0ea4446e","uuid":"30a4a58c-0f2f-4a82-82c4-55bc9208f009"}
